TT-Atom is an independent implementation of the eSEN / eSCN-MD (UMA-family)
equivariant machine-learning interatomic potential architecture for Tenstorrent
hardware via ttnn. It does NOT include any model weights.

The eSEN / eSCN-MD architecture and the reference implementation (fairchem-core)
are developed by the FAIR Chemistry team at Meta. UMA and eSEN model checkpoints
are distributed separately by Meta under their own licenses (e.g. the FAIR
Chemistry License / OMat24 terms) and are NOT redistributed here. Users must
obtain a checkpoint directly from the original source and comply with its license.

fairchem-core (https://github.com/FAIR-Chem/fairchem) is licensed under the MIT
License and is an optional dependency, used only for checkpoint loading and for
generating golden reference tensors.
